April 11 (Reuters) - Brazilian airline Gol SA (GOLL4.SA) said on Monday it expects to report a loss of 1.98 real per share in the first quarter of 2022 and a loss of 78 cents per American Depositary Share. The company also said its earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (EBITDA) margin should be at about 11% in the quarter. Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.